I like the `#` prefix, it makes it stand out better. The reasons are pretty straightforward to follow, as well. Also, thanks for the more comprehensive list of reasons. I think there's also

    // "defer func ..."
    // "defer func arg"
    // "defer func"

By the way, what does it mean that you didn't find coverage on the last set of reasons? Some of them look like they're the same, but spelled differently; `slice-literal-element` vs `slice literal element`, for example. Also, what's the difference between a pointer literal escaping via the assign phase vs the flood phase?
